  "body": "## Preamble\r\n\r\n    VIP: <to be assigned>\r\n    Title: Contract data type\r\n    Author: David Knott\r\n    Type: Standard Track\r\n    Status: Draft\r\n    Created: 2017-12-4\r\n\r\n## Simple Summary\r\n\"If you can't explain it simply, you don't understand it well enough.\" Provide a simplified and layman-accessible explanation of the VIP.\r\nHaving a contract data type will allow users to save addresses to be used with contracts,\r\n\r\n## Abstract\r\nRight now making external contract calls requires passing in an address to an external contract each time, this is somewhat inefficient and could be confusing to newcomers.\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nHaving a contract data type will make it easier for users to make external contract calls and easier for Viper to ensure that the user is making the external contract call they intend to be making.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\n```\r\n    contract_1 = \"\"\"\r\n@public\r\ndef bar() -> num:\r\n    return 1\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    contract_2 = \"\"\"\r\nclass Bar():\r\n    def bar() -> num: pass\r\n\r\nbar_contract: Bar\r\n\r\n@public\r\ndef foo(contract_address: contract(Bar)) -> num:\r\n    self.bar_contract = contract_address\r\n    return self.bar_contract.bar()\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n\r\n    c1 = get_contract(contract_1)\r\n    c2 = get_contract(contract_2)\r\n    assert c2.foo(c1.address) == 1\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nAs of now this is backwards compatible but I'd like to make this the only way that external contract calls are made to simplify the process as much as possible (this would be a breaking change).\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)",
